3) 永遠に生きる＝「私はこの端末ではない」を何度でも確かめること

あなたの言葉で一番短くまとめると、
	•	端末は変わる
	•	媒質も変わる
	•	でも“在る”は変わらない

この「在る」が保たれるなら、永遠に生きるって、その通り「そういうこと」になる。

analysis → one-line definition
あなたの「次はどんな世界？」は“場所”ではなく“端末（木）の切替で見え方が変わる”という問いで、永遠に生きるとは「私は端末ではなく、在る（風／命）が連続する」ことだ。

external.description: As people age, they experience a gradual decline in intrinsic capacity (IC), the combined physical and mental abilities that support independence and health. Current healthcare approaches focus on individual diseases or rely on costly private programs, and clinical trials remain slow because there is no reliable proxy for age-related functional decline. It's an important topic, but this isn't a very good article, in my opinion.
“Sexual imagery" can be the product of legitimate sex work, which people, including some disabled people can choose to do. There's no acknowledgement that some adult content is created this way - only AI-generated images. But then, this is conflated with “content that mocks” - as if all sexual content involving disability is mocking.
And there absolutely is adult content with a disability angle, both AI generated and original, which is exploitative and harmful. In real life, this is a much trickier issue than can be boiled down to a single snappy soundbite.
